 look like mistakes. You will buy a pocket of anonymity with hush-ink and good coin, and you will let a pair of lantern-bearers guide you through ring-teeth at a low that bites ankles but spares knees. At the gyre’s edge, you will play the Vent-Wind Flute not as a note but as a question, drawing the command to answer and then letting it spill into the Maw’s hum where answers go to drown. You will keep your silt-bell ready to pin any last stubbornness to the water’s surface, long enough for the tide to iron it smooth. You will return with a shard that no longer sings but still remembers shapes, and you will carry it in Glassthread gloves straight to Miren before the Bazaar can name a price for something it cannot hear.\", \"outcome\": \"The Syndicate’s guidance is eerie and effective, and their skiff skips through coral jaws that would have sheared a lesser helmsman while your breath stays measured. The command’s motif stretches thin in the gyre’s spin and frays into threads, each one swallowed by a silence that does not echo, until only the shape of an order remains like a story missing its verbs. You cut a safe shard and cast the rest to the Maw, and for a heartbeat you feel the city’s bells on your skin as if testing whether to ring once or not at all. Jath Pell scowls at the Syndicate scent on your cloak but cannot argue with success, and Miren says a knot is a knot no matter who points out the loops. Word of the gyre-ride becomes a rumor sold and resold in the Night Bazaar, but the rewards still reach your hands, and the horn-barge does not learn arrogance from an easy victory.\"}\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M3\", \"M7\"], \"next\": [\"M9\", \"M11\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"item\", \"description\": \"Elder Chain Shard (consumable; cancels one magical command or compulsion). Miren returns a harmlessly attuned splinter as a controlled tool after secure storage is arranged.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"reputation\", \"desc